# .trivyignore — acknowledged CVE exceptions for Trivy scans.
#
# Add entries here only after manual triage confirms a finding is either:
#   - a false positive
#   - has no fix available and risk is accepted with a linked issue
#
# Format:
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN  # reason — expires: YYYY-MM-DD  issue: #NNN
#
# Example (commented out):
#   CVE-2023-12345  # false positive in apk metadata — expires: 2025-12-31  issue: #42

# OpenBao v2.5.3 is the latest release as of 2026-05-11 and is newer than these fixed versions;
# Trivy sees the bao binary's embedded OpenBao module as a pseudo-version.
CVE-2024-8185   # false positive: bao v2.5.3 >= fixed 2.0.3 — expires: 2026-08-11
CVE-2024-9180   # false positive: bao v2.5.3 >= fixed 2.0.3 — expires: 2026-08-11
CVE-2025-59043  # false positive: bao v2.5.3 >= fixed 2.4.1 — expires: 2026-08-11
CVE-2025-64761  # false positive: bao v2.5.3 >= fixed 2.4.4 — expires: 2026-08-11

# smallstep/cli v0.30.2 is the latest release as of 2026-05-11 and still embeds these
# vulnerable Go modules/stdlib versions. Recheck when the next step release lands.
CVE-2026-34986  # accepted risk: no newer official step release — expires: 2026-06-30
CVE-2026-33816  # accepted risk: no newer official step release — expires: 2026-06-30
CVE-2026-29181  # accepted risk: no newer official step release — expires: 2026-06-30
